â™«<i> Below the white clouds run horses </i>â™«

303
00:24:59.080 --> 00:25:07.480
â™«<i>I swing my horsewhip and the crack travels far and wide</i>â™«

304
00:25:08.640 --> 00:25:13.140
<i>Ye Wenjie and I have redrafted the letter.</i>

305
00:25:15.400 --> 00:25:19.160
<i>Ye Wenjie, read it.</i>

306
00:25:24.900 --> 00:25:28.280
<i>[PLA Letter Paper]</i>

307
00:25:31.590 --> 00:25:36.640
<i>"We extend our best wishes to you, inhabitants of another world.</i>

308
00:25:36.640 --> 00:25:38.850
<i>After reading the following message,</i>

309
00:25:38.850 --> 00:25:42.940
<i>you should have a basic understanding of civilization on Earth.</i>

310
00:25:43.740 --> 00:25:49.250
<i>By dint of long toil and creativity, the human race has built a splendid civilization,</i>

311
00:25:49.250 --> 00:25:51.940
<i>blossoming with diverse cultures.</i>

312
00:25:51.940 --> 00:25:57.370
<i>We're also getting to know the laws of nature and the development of human societies.</i>

313
00:25:57.370 --> 00:25:59.740
<i>We cherish all that we've accomplished.</i>

314
00:25:59.740 --> 00:26:02.750
<i>But our world is still flawed.</i>

315
00:26:02.750 --> 00:26:08.930
<i>Hate exists, as do prejudice and war.</i>

316
00:26:08.930 --> 00:26:11.480
<i>Contradictive productive forces and relations </i>

317
00:26:11.480 --> 00:26:14.260
<i>are causing extremely uneven distribution of wealth.</i>

318
00:26:14.260 --> 00:26:19.130
<i>And large portions of humanity are living in poverty and misery.</i>

319
00:26:19.130 --> 00:26:23.890
<i>Human societies are working hard to resolve the difficulties they face,</i>

320
00:26:23.890 --> 00:26:27.690
<i>striving to create a better future for Earth civilization.</i>

321
00:26:27.690 --> 00:26:33.500
<i>The country that sent this message is also engaged in this effort.</i>

322
00:26:33.500 --> 00:26:36.590
<i>We are dedicated to building an ideal society</i>

323
00:26:36.590 --> 00:26:41.820
<i>where the labor and value of every human are fully respected,</i>

324
00:26:41.820 --> 00:26:47.410
<i>and everyone's material and spiritual needs are fully met</i>

325
00:26:47.410 --> 00:26:50.790
<i>so that civilization on Earth may become more perfect.</i>

326
00:26:50.790 --> 00:26:54.440
<i>With the best of intentions, we look forward to establishing contact</i>

327
00:26:54.440 --> 00:26:57.950
<i>with other civilized societies in the universe.</i>

328
00:26:57.950 --> 00:27:00.370
<i>We look forward to working with you</i>

329
00:27:00.370 --> 00:27:06.190
<i>to build a better life in this vast universe."</i>

330
00:27:06.190 --> 00:27:12.600
This letter of humans' best wishes was sent to the universe.

331
00:27:13.690 --> 00:27:18.400
Enclosed was an overview of Earth,

332
00:27:18.410 --> 00:27:21.410
life on Earth,

333
00:27:21.410 --> 00:27:27.170
and human society as well as basic world history.

334
00:27:27.170 --> 00:27:32.380
All that was sent after transmitting the Self-interpreting Code System.

335
00:27:34.260 --> 00:27:37.330
Red Coast is a great project, no doubt.

336
00:27:40.300 --> 00:27:43.980
When sending messages to the universe,

337
00:27:45.210 --> 00:27:47.960
how did you ensure our security?

338
00:27:47.960 --> 00:27:54.400
It was carefully vetted to ensure that it didn't give away

339
00:27:54.400 --> 00:27:59.820
the Earth's coordinates relative to the Milky Way.

340
00:27:59.820 --> 00:28:06.450
At the 2,280 MHz, 12,000 MHz, and 22,000 MHz channels,

341
00:28:06.450 --> 00:28:11.260
the transmission times of the message were

342
00:28:11.260 --> 00:28:16.540
31 minutes, 7.5 minutes, and 3.5 minutes respectively.

343
00:28:16.540 --> 00:28:21.870
Transmission at the higher-frequency 12,000 MHz and 22,000 MHz channels

344
00:28:21.870 --> 00:28:27.860
was minimized in case our location was exposed.

345
00:28:29.350 --> 00:28:32.180
Back in those days,

346
00:28:32.180 --> 00:28:38.320
SETI at Red Coast was marginalized research.

347
00:28:38.320 --> 00:28:41.750
But why such a high security rating?

348
00:28:43.260 --> 00:28:48.820
They asked the same question at the very beginning of the Project

349
00:28:48.820 --> 00:28:54.010
and it was asked until the very end.

350
00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:59.440
But now, you should have the answer.

351
00:29:00.810 --> 00:29:08.010
We can only marvel at the foresight of the top decision-maker of the Project.

352
00:29:10.060 --> 00:29:12.690
Had Red Coast succeeded,

353
00:29:13.790 --> 00:29:16.740
the world would be utterly different.

354
00:29:18.970 --> 00:29:24.980
Well, it's still too soon to tell whether it succeeded or not.

355
00:29:24.980 --> 00:29:32.570
The radio waves sent out haven't gone too far in the universe yet.

356
00:29:32.570 --> 00:29:37.210
The farther the signals travel, the weaker they become,

357
00:29:37.210 --> 00:29:43.690
and the less likely that any extraterrestrial civilization will receive them.

358
00:29:45.170 --> 00:29:50.990
In order for extraterrestrials to detect our signals,

359
00:29:50.990 --> 00:29:56.890
we broadcast at a power level equal to the energy output of a mid-sized star.

360
00:29:56.890 --> 00:30:00.200
Soviet astrophysicist Nicolai Kardashev once proposed

361
00:30:00.200 --> 00:30:03.100
that we could divide civilizations

362
00:30:03.100 --> 00:30:07.930
based on the power they could command for communication purposes,

363
00:30:07.930 --> 00:30:10.890
He divided them into three types:

364
00:30:10.890 --> 00:30:17.040
A Type I civilization can muster an amount of energy equal to the total output of the Earth.

365
00:30:17.040 --> 00:30:23.000
A Type II civilization can marshal the energy equal to the output of a typical star.

366
00:30:24.010 --> 00:30:29.500
A Type III civilization can utilize its communication energy equal to the energy output of a galaxy.

367
00:30:30.210 --> 00:30:35.580
Civilization on Earth is currently not even a full Type I.

368
00:30:35.580 --> 00:30:39.310
And the transmissions from Red Coast used only about one ten-thousandth

369
00:30:39.310 --> 00:30:43.230
of the power the Earth could muster.

370
00:30:43.230 --> 00:30:45.710
Our call wasn't any louder

371
00:30:46.970 --> 00:30:52.310
than the buzzing of a mosquito.

372
00:30:52.310 --> 00:30:54.780
No one could hear it.

373
00:30:54.780 --> 00:30:58.740
But the Type II and III civilizations Kardashev proposed do exist,

374
00:30:58.740 --> 00:31:01.800
we should be able to hear them by now.

375
00:31:03.050 --> 00:31:08.400
In this case, our efforts seem to have only proven one thing

376
00:31:08.400 --> 00:31:13.920
that in the vast universe, only the Earth has intelligent life.

377
00:31:18.450 --> 00:31:24.580
Theoretically, there might never be a definitive answer to that question.

378
00:31:25.340 --> 00:31:27.640
But emotionally,

379
00:31:27.640 --> 00:31:33.550
I and everyone else who went through Red Coast

380
00:31:33.550 --> 00:31:36.080
all believed so.

381
00:31:38.500 --> 00:31:40.960
Too bad the Project was decommissioned.

382
00:31:40.960 --> 00:31:45.600
It was there already and should've kept going.

383
00:31:47.410 --> 00:31:50.410
It was a great cause worth fighting for.

384
00:31:53.790 --> 00:31:56.280
In the late 70s,

385
00:31:56.700 --> 00:32:01.840
there was a large-scale renovation.

386
00:32:19.500 --> 00:32:23.350
The transmission system was automated.

387
00:32:23.350 --> 00:32:27.510
Data processing of monitoring became far more advanced.

388
00:32:27.510 --> 00:32:31.550
40,000 channels could be monitored simultaneously.

389
00:32:31.550 --> 00:32:38.930
The more people knew, the clearer they became about the difficulty of SETI.

390
00:32:38.930 --> 00:32:44.650
And the leadership lost interest in Red Coast.

391
00:32:46.580 --> 00:32:48.650
After the renovation,

392
00:32:48.650 --> 00:32:53.680
the first change we experienced was lowered security rating.

393
00:32:53.680 --> 00:32:58.750
The security detail was reduced to a group of five guards.

394
00:32:58.750 --> 00:33:00.580
Salute!

395
00:33:01.790 --> 00:33:05.830
Red Coast remained within the Second Artillery Corps,

396
00:33:05.830 --> 00:33:11.290
but management of its scientific activities was turned over to the Astronomy Institute of Chinese Academy of Sciences.

397
00:33:11.290 --> 00:33:17.960
and it took on some research projects that had nothing to do with SETI.

398
00:33:17.960 --> 00:33:22.830
I believe you achieved most of your accomplishments then.

399
00:33:27.210 --> 00:33:33.070
At the time, we had China's largest radio telescope.

400
00:33:33.070 --> 00:33:38.650
Following all those changes, we first took on some radio astronomy projects.

401
00:33:38.650 --> 00:33:43.640
Later, more and more such observatories were built,

402
00:33:43.640 --> 00:33:46.680
and Red Coast shifted to the observation and

403
00:33:46.680 --> 00:33:50.820
analysis of solar electromagnetic activity

404
00:33:50.820 --> 00:33:55.350
with an added solar telescope.

405
00:33:55.350 --> 00:33:58.820
I bet practical applications were a ton.

406
00:33:58.820 --> 00:34:00.270
Correct.

407
00:34:00.270 --> 00:34:04.640
The mathematical model we built for solar electromagnetic activity

408
00:34:04.640 --> 00:34:08.670
was state-of-the-art.

409
00:34:08.670 --> 00:34:12.550
With such fruition, the large investment in Red Coast

410
00:34:12.550 --> 00:34:15.670
saw a little bit of return.

411
00:34:15.670 --> 00:34:22.110
Actually, much of the credit should go to Political Commissar Lei,

412
00:34:22.110 --> 00:34:26.480
although he did have his own agenda, too.

413
00:34:26.480 --> 00:34:28.330
Political Commissar Lei?

414
00:34:29.390 --> 00:34:33.360
Wasn't he a political officer in that technical unit?

415
00:34:33.360 --> 00:34:38.810
Before enlisting, he had studied astrophysics as well.

416
00:34:38.810 --> 00:34:45.980
Research projects we took on outside of SETI were all due to his efforts.

417
00:34:49.480 --> 00:34:54.590
It wasn't easy to return to technical work.

418
00:34:54.590 --> 00:35:00.310
Without Lei, Red Coast would've been long gone.

419
00:35:01.110 --> 00:35:04.790
When it was converted for civil use,

420
00:35:04.800 --> 00:35:08.840
the military basically abandoned it.

421
00:35:08.840 --> 00:35:14.150
Chinese Academy of Sciences could no longer keep the base running.

422
00:35:14.150 --> 00:35:19.630
Inevitably, it was shut down.

423
00:35:59.210 --> 00:36:05.130
In the dead of the night, when I was alone

424
00:36:05.130 --> 00:36:07.610
in the empty monitoring room,

425
00:36:07.610 --> 00:36:14.730
I could hear in my headphones the lifeless noise of the universe.

426
00:36:15.270 --> 00:36:19.800
It was faint but continuous,

427
00:36:20.260 --> 00:36:22.840
more eternal than the stars.

428
00:36:24.730 --> 00:36:29.420
Sometimes I thought it sounded like

429
00:36:30.300 --> 00:36:35.260
the endless cold winds of Radar Peak.

430
00:36:36.000 --> 00:36:38.330
I was chilled to the bone.

431
00:36:40.360 --> 00:36:42.410
There weren't enough words

432
00:36:43.660 --> 00:36:47.460
to describe such loneliness.

433
00:36:49.400 --> 00:36:55.630
SETI is quite a unique discipline.

434
00:36:55.630 --> 00:37:02.230
It can shape researchers' perspectives on life.

435
00:37:03.510 --> 00:37:12.620
It occurred to me repeatedly that life was truly an accident among all the accidents in the universe.

436
00:37:13.380 --> 00:37:19.100
And the universe was an empty palace

437
00:37:19.880 --> 00:37:27.690
in which humankind was the only ant.

438
00:37:53.020 --> 00:37:59.490
This kind of thinking made me live a conflicted life since.

439
00:38:00.770 --> 00:38:05.550
Sometimes I thought life was precious

440
00:38:05.550 --> 00:38:09.250
and more important than anything.

441
00:38:10.320 --> 00:38:13.130
But other times,

442
00:38:13.130 --> 00:38:19.860
I found humans so insignificant that nothing was worthwhile.

443
00:38:19.860 --> 00:38:25.030
Anyway, despite such internal conflicts,

444
00:38:25.030 --> 00:38:27.480
my life slipped away,

445
00:38:28.350 --> 00:38:33.370
and before I knew it, I was already old.

446
00:38:43.510 --> 00:38:48.510
I'm not getting any younger or healthier.

447
00:38:49.020 --> 00:38:51.320
I can't predict the future.

448
00:38:52.540 --> 00:38:57.600
All I can do is live my life as it is.

